08/12/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Michael Humphreys, head of the European Commission delegation to BiH, said Tuesday (7 December) that there could be no talks on completing the Stabilisation and Association Process until the UN war crimes tribunal says Republika Srpska (RS) is co-operating with it.
Humphreys visited Banja Luka to discuss the implementation of reforms and Euro-Atlantic integration efforts with RS Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic and Parliament Speaker Dragan Stojcic.
(Tanjug, Vjesti - 08/12/04;
PBS BiH, RS Government Web site - 07/12/04)
